 To find how many inches are in $2 \frac{1}{6}$ yards, we have to multiply $2 \frac{1}{6}$ yards by $36$ inches per yard, since there are $36$ inches in a yard. We can convert the mixed number to an improper fraction, so $2 \frac{1}{6}$ word combines are
\begin{align*} 2 \frac{1}{6} &= \frac{13}{6} \end{align*}
Whatever fraction we multiply our number by, the result is that number multiplied by the fraction. So $\frac16$ is one of the fraction’s parts, whereas $36$ inches are all the parts arranged on a line. Thus, we have
\begin{align*}
\text{How many inches does one yard contain} &= 36\ \text{inches} \\
\text{How many inches does one-sixth part of a yard contain} &= 6\ \text{inches} \\
\text{Since } 1 \frac{13}{6} \text{ = 2 \frac{1}{6}} &= \boxed{6 \text{  inches per part}}.
\end{align*}
Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{234}$ inches. </think> <answer> 234 </answer>

